What do I have to do so that I can track my game?
2. Download and install the Npcap installer:
3. Start the Statistics Analyses Tool (Restart once)
5. Select Tracking from the drop-down menu
6. Click on the large ON/OFF button to start tracking. If the button is blue and the circle is on the right, tracking is activated.

7. If the tracker does not yet have all the important information, the wifi icon is yellow. In order for it to turn green, your character has to change a map once in the game. (e.g. Martlock to Eldon Hill)
8. If the wifi icon is green and your character name can be seen, the tracker is fully functional - Done!

The crafting bonus is the bonus of the city or Hideout you are crafting in.
To find the number you need to open the mini-map and hover over the top right corner where you can see what bonus this city/HO gives.
In a city like Lymhurst it's 118%. If the city gives a bonus to the item to be crafted, it's 133%. In Hideouts it can be higher, also there can be a Daily Bonus which can be 10% or 20%.
The auction house setup fee and taxes can be found in-game when you want to sell an item on the market.
If you have Premium, you can leave the two values as they are. If you want to sell something manually, set both to 0. If you don't have a premium, the values are usually twice as high.
